<file path="docs/testing.md">
  1: # Testing Guide
  2: 
  3: ## Quick Start
  4: 
  5: ```bash
  6: npm test                 # Unit tests (no auth required)
  7: npm run test:integration # Integration tests (requires Google auth)
  8: npm run test:all         # All tests (requires Google auth + LLM API keys)
  9: ```
 10: 
 11: ## Test Structure
 12: 
 13: - `src/tests/unit/` - Unit tests (mocked, no external dependencies)
 14: - `src/tests/integration/` - Integration tests (real Google Calendar API calls)
 15: 
 16: ## Unit Tests
 17: 
 18: **Requirements:** None - fully self-contained
 19: 
 20: **Coverage:**
 21: - Request validation and schema compliance
 22: - Error handling and edge cases
 23: - Date/time parsing and timezone conversion logic
 24: - Mock-based handler functionality
 25: - Tool registration and validation
 26: 
 27: **Run with:**
 28: ```bash
 29: npm test
 30: ```
 31: 
 32: ## Integration Tests
 33: 
 34: Integration tests are divided into three categories based on their requirements:
 35: 
 36: ### 1. Direct Google Calendar Integration
 37: 
 38: **Files:** `direct-integration.test.ts`
 39: 
 40: **Requirements:**
 41: - Google OAuth credentials file
 42: - Authenticated test account
 43: - Real Google Calendar access
 44: 
 45: **Setup:**
 46: ```bash
 47: # Set environment variables
 48: export GOOGLE_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS="path/to/your/oauth-credentials.json"
 49: export TEST_CALENDAR_ID="your-test-calendar-id"
 50: 
 51: # Authenticate test account
 52: npm run dev auth:test
 53: ```
 54: 
 55: **What these tests do:**
 56: - ✅ Create, read, update, delete real calendar events
 57: - ✅ Test multi-calendar operations with batch requests
 58: - ✅ Validate timezone handling with actual Google Calendar API
 59: - ✅ Test recurring event patterns and modifications
 60: - ✅ Verify free/busy queries and calendar listings
 61: - ✅ Performance benchmarking with real API latency
 62: 
 63: **⚠️ Warning:** These tests modify real calendar data in your test calendar.
 64: 
 65: ### 2. LLM Integration Tests
 66: 
 67: **Files:** `claude-mcp-integration.test.ts`, `openai-mcp-integration.test.ts`
 68: 
 69: **Requirements:**
 70: - Google OAuth credentials + authenticated test account (from above)
 71: - LLM API keys
 72: - **LLM models that support MCP (Claude) or function calling (OpenAI)**
 73: 
 74: **Additional setup:**
 75: ```bash
 76: # Set LLM API keys
 77: export CLAUDE_API_KEY="your-claude-api-key"
 78: export OPENAI_API_KEY="your-openai-api-key"
 79: 
 80: # Optional: specify models (must support MCP/function calling)
 81: export ANTHROPIC_MODEL="claude-3-5-haiku-20241022"  # Default
 82: export OPENAI_MODEL="gpt-4o-mini"                   # Default
 83: ```
 84: 
 85: **What these tests do:**
 86: - ✅ Test end-to-end MCP protocol integration with Claude
 87: - ✅ Test end-to-end MCP protocol integration with OpenAI
 88: - ✅ Validate AI assistant can successfully call calendar tools
 89: - ✅ Test complex multi-step AI workflows
 90: 
 91: **⚠️ Warning:** These tests consume LLM API credits and modify real calendar data.
 92: 
 93: **Important LLM Compatibility Notes:**
 94: - **Claude**: Only Claude 3.5+ models support MCP. Earlier models will fail.
 95: - **OpenAI**: Only GPT-4+ and select GPT-3.5-turbo models support function calling.
 96: - If you see "tool not found" or "function not supported" errors, verify your model selection.
 97: 
 98: ### Running Specific Integration Test Types
 99: 
100: ```bash
101: # Run only direct Google Calendar integration tests
102: npm run test:integration -- direct-integration.test.ts
103: 
104: # Run only LLM integration tests (requires API keys)
105: npm run test:integration -- claude-mcp-integration.test.ts
106: npm run test:integration -- openai-mcp-integration.test.ts
107: 
108: # Run all integration tests (requires both Google auth + LLM API keys)
109: npm run test:integration
110: ```
111: 
112: ## Environment Configuration
113: 
114: ### Required Environment Variables
115: 
116: | Variable | Required For | Purpose | Example |
117: |----------|--------------|---------|---------|
118: | `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS` | All integration tests | Path to OAuth credentials file | `./gcp-oauth.keys.json` |
119: | `TEST_CALENDAR_ID` | All integration tests | Target calendar for test operations | `test-calendar@gmail.com` or `primary` |
120: | `CLAUDE_API_KEY` | Claude integration tests | Anthropic API access | `sk-ant-api03-...` |
121: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | OpenAI integration tests | OpenAI API access | `sk-...` |
122: | `INVITEE_1` | Attendee tests | Test attendee email | `test1@example.com` |
123: | `INVITEE_2` | Attendee tests | Test attendee email | `test2@example.com` |
124: 
125: ### Optional Environment Variables
126: 
127: | Variable | Purpose | Default | Notes |
128: |----------|---------|---------|-------|
129: | `GOOGLE_ACCOUNT_MODE` | Account mode | `normal` | Use `test` for testing |
130: | `DEBUG_LLM_INTERACTIONS` | Debug logging | `false` | Set `true` for verbose LLM logs |
131: | `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` | Claude model | `claude-3-5-haiku-20241022` | Must support MCP |
132: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | OpenAI model | `gpt-4o-mini` | Must support function calling |
133: 
134: ### Complete Setup Example
135: 
136: 1. **Create `.env` file in project root:**
137: ```env
138: # Required for all integration tests
139: GOOGLE_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS=./gcp-oauth.keys.json
140: TEST_CALENDAR_ID=test-calendar@gmail.com
141: 
142: # Required for LLM integration tests
143: CLAUDE_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-...
144: OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
145: 
146: # Required for attendee tests
147: INVITEE_1=test1@example.com
148: INVITEE_2=test2@example.com
149: 
150: # Optional configurations
151: GOOGLE_ACCOUNT_MODE=test
152: DEBUG_LLM_INTERACTIONS=false
153: ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-3-5-haiku-20241022
154: OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
155: ```
156: 
157: 2. **Obtain Google OAuth Credentials:**
158:    - Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com)
159:    - Create a new project or select existing
160:    - Enable Google Calendar API
161:    - Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (Desktop app type)
162:    - Download credentials JSON file
163:    - Save as `gcp-oauth.keys.json` in project root
164: 
165: 3. **Authenticate Test Account:**
166: ```bash
167: # Creates tokens in ~/.config/google-calendar-mcp/tokens.json
168: npm run dev auth:test
169: ```
170: 
171: 4. **Verify Setup:**
172: ```bash
173: # Check authentication status
174: npm run dev account:status
175: 
176: # Run a simple integration test
177: npm run test:integration -- direct-integration.test.ts
178: ```
179: 
180: 
181: ## Troubleshooting
182: 
183: ### Common Issues
184: 
185: **Authentication Errors:**
186: - **"No credentials found"**: Run `npm run dev auth:test` to authenticate
187: - **"Token expired"**: Re-authenticate with `npm run dev auth:test`
188: - **"Invalid credentials"**: Check `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS` path is correct
189: - **"Refresh token must be passed"**: Delete tokens and re-authenticate
190: 
191: **API Errors:**
192: - **Rate limits**: Tests include retry logic, but may still hit limits with frequent runs
193: - **Calendar not found**: Verify `TEST_CALENDAR_ID` exists and is accessible
194: - **Permission denied**: Ensure test account has write access to the calendar
195: - **"Invalid time range"**: Free/busy queries limited to 3 months between timeMin and timeMax
196: 
197: **LLM Integration Errors:**
198: - **"Invalid API key"**: Check `CLAUDE_API_KEY`/`OPENAI_API_KEY` are set correctly
199: - **"Insufficient credits"**: LLM tests consume API credits - ensure account has balance
200: - **"Model not found"**: Verify model name and availability in your API plan
201: - **"Tool not found" or "Function not supported"**: 
202:   - Claude: Ensure using Claude 3.5+ model that supports MCP
203:   - OpenAI: Ensure using GPT-4+ or compatible GPT-3.5-turbo model
204: - **"Maximum tokens exceeded"**: Some complex tests may hit token limits with verbose models
205: - **Network timeouts**: LLM tests may take 2-5 minutes due to AI processing time
206: 
207: ### Test Data Management
208: 
209: **Calendar Cleanup:**
210: - Tests attempt to clean up created events automatically
211: - Failed tests may leave test events in your calendar
212: - Manually delete events with "Integration Test" or "Test Event" in the title if needed
213: 
214: **Test Isolation:**
215: - Use a dedicated test calendar (`TEST_CALENDAR_ID`)
216: - Don't use your personal calendar for testing
217: - Consider creating a separate Google account for testing
218: 
219: ### Performance Considerations
220: 
221: **Test Duration:**
222: - Unit tests: ~2 seconds
223: - Direct integration tests: ~30-60 seconds  
224: - LLM integration tests: ~2-5 minutes (due to AI processing)
225: - Full test suite: ~5-10 minutes
226: 
227: **Parallel Execution:**
228: - Unit tests run in parallel by default
229: - Integration tests run sequentially to avoid API conflicts
230: - Use `--reporter=verbose` for detailed progress during long test runs
231: 
232: ## Development Tips
233: 
234: ### Debugging Integration Tests
235: 
236: 1. **Enable Debug Logging:**
237: ```bash
238: # Debug all LLM interactions
239: export DEBUG_LLM_INTERACTIONS=true
240: 
241: # Debug MCP server
242: export DEBUG=mcp:*
243: ```
244: 
245: 2. **Run Single Test:**
246: ```bash
247: # Run specific test by name pattern
248: npm run test:integration -- -t "should handle timezone"
249: ```
250: 
251: 3. **Interactive Testing:**
252: ```bash
253: # Use the dev menu for quick access to test commands
254: npm run dev
255: ```
256: 
257: ### Writing New Integration Tests
258: 
259: 1. **Use Test Data Factory:**
260: ```typescript
261: import { TestDataFactory } from './test-data-factory.js';
262: 
263: const factory = new TestDataFactory();
264: const testEvent = factory.createTestEvent({
265:   summary: 'My Test Event',
266:   start: factory.getTomorrowAt(14, 0),
267:   end: factory.getTomorrowAt(15, 0)
268: });
269: ```
270: 
271: 2. **Track Created Events:**
272: ```typescript
273: // Events are automatically tracked for cleanup
274: const eventId = TestDataFactory.extractEventIdFromResponse(result);
275: ```
276: 
277: 3. **LLM Context Logging:**
278: ```typescript
279: // Wrap LLM operations for automatic error logging
280: await executeWithContextLogging('Test Name', async () => {
281:   const response = await llmClient.sendMessage('...');
282:   // Test assertions
283: });
284: ```
285: 
286: ### Best Practices
287: 
288: 1. **Environment Isolation:**
289:    - Always use `GOOGLE_ACCOUNT_MODE=test` for testing
290:    - Use a dedicated test calendar, not personal calendar
291:    - Consider separate Google account for testing
292: 
293: 2. **Cost Management:**
294:    - LLM tests consume API credits
295:    - Run specific tests during development
296:    - Use smaller/cheaper models for initial testing
297: 
298: 3. **Test Data:**
299:    - Tests auto-cleanup created events
300:    - Use unique event titles with timestamps
301:    - Verify cleanup in afterEach hooks
302: 
303: 4. **Debugging Failures:**
304:    - Check `DEBUG_LLM_INTERACTIONS` output for LLM tests
305:    - Verify model compatibility for tool/function support
306:    - Check API quotas and rate limits
