<file path="docs/SCHEMA-ORG-ALIGNMENT.md">
  1: # Schema.org Type Alignment Analysis
  2: ## Google Calendar MCP Codebase Type Definitions
  3: 
  4: **Generated**: 2026-03-24
  5: **Purpose**: Align Google Calendar MCP type definitions with schema.org vocabulary for semantic web compatibility and metadata standardization.
  6: 
  7: ---
  8: 
  9: ## Executive Summary
 10: 
 11: The Google Calendar MCP codebase defines **47 TypeScript types and interfaces** across calendar, email/Gmail, conflict detection, and transport management. This document maps these types to **schema.org vocabulary** for:
 12: 
 13: - **Semantic interoperability**: Align internal types with globally-recognized schema standards
 14: - **Structured data compatibility**: Enable rich metadata and knowledge graph integration
 15: - **API documentation**: Use schema.org descriptions to enhance API reference
 16: - **SEO/LLM benefits**: Improve content discoverability and AI understanding
 17: 
 18: **Key Finding**: The codebase aligns well with schema.org's **Event**, **EmailMessage**, **Action**, and **Schedule** types, with opportunities to enhance conflict/duplicate detection with custom extensions.
 19: 
 20: ---
 21: 
 22: ## Codebase Type Inventory
 23: 
 24: ### Core Calendar Types (7 types)
 25: 
 26: | Codebase Type | Purpose | Schema.org Equivalent |
 27: |---|---|---|
 28: | **CalendarEvent** | Main event entity with start/end times, attendees, reminders | [`Event`](https://schema.org/Event) |
 29: | **CalendarListEntry** | Calendar metadata in calendar list | [`Calendar`](https://schema.org/Calendar) or `Collection` |
 30: | **CalendarEventAttendee** | Event participant with RSVP status | [`Person`](https://schema.org/Person) + [`Reservation`](https://schema.org/Reservation) |
 31: | **CalendarEventReminder** | Notification settings (email/popup, minutes) | [`InteractionCounter`](https://schema.org/InteractionCounter) or custom reminder action |
 32: | **FreeBusyResponse** | Free/busy time slots | [`ScheduleAction`](https://schema.org/ScheduleAction) + time range |
 33: | **EventTimeRange** | Start/end time for events | [`OpeningHoursSpecification`](https://schema.org/OpeningHoursSpecification) |
 34: | **DateTimeComponents** | Year, month, day, hour breakdown | Utility type (no direct schema equivalent) |
 35: 
 36: ### Conflict Detection Types (4 types)
 37: 
 38: | Codebase Type | Purpose | Schema.org Alignment |
 39: |---|---|---|
 40: | **ConflictInfo** | Overlap or duplicate event record | Custom extension of [`Event`](https://schema.org/Event) with conflict metadata |
 41: | **DuplicateInfo** | Duplicate event detected | Custom extension; could use [`Thing`](https://schema.org/Thing) with identical properties |
 42: | **ConflictCheckResult** | Result of conflict detection | Custom `ConflictCheckResult` type (MCP-specific) |
 43: | **ConflictDetectionOptions** | Configuration for conflict checking | Custom configuration object |
 44: 
 45: ### Gmail/Email Types (7 types)
 46: 
 47: | Codebase Type | Purpose | Schema.org Equivalent |
 48: |---|---|---|
 49: | **GmailSearchInput** | Email search query parameters | Custom MCP input type; uses [`SearchAction`](https://schema.org/SearchAction) pattern |
 50: | **GmailModifyInput** | Message modification (mark read, archive, delete) | [`ModifyAction`](https://schema.org/ModifyAction) or custom action |
 51: | **GmailCreateFilterInput** | Email filter criteria | Custom filter configuration |
 52: | **GmailApplyFiltersInput** | Apply filters to messages | Custom action; relates to [`FilterAction`](https://schema.org/FilterAction) (experimental) |
 53: | **GmailCreateLabelInput** | Gmail label creation | Custom label/tag type; could extend [`Thing`](https://schema.org/Thing) with name + visibility |
 54: | **OAuthCredentials** | Authentication tokens | No schema.org equivalent (authentication is out of scope) |
 55: | **PerformanceMetric** | Operation timing metadata | [`PerformanceMetric`](https://schema.org/PerformanceMetric) |
 56: 
 57: ### Transport & Configuration Types (8 types)
 58: 
 59: | Codebase Type | Purpose | Schema.org Alignment |
 60: |---|---|---|
 61: | **TransportConfig** | Transport layer configuration (stdio/http) | MCP-specific, no schema.org equivalent |
 62: | **ServerConfig** | Server configuration | MCP-specific, no schema.org equivalent |
 63: | **BatchRequest** / **BatchResponse** | Batch operation handling | [`BuyAction`](https://schema.org/BuyAction) pattern or custom batch action |
 64: | **BatchError** | Batch operation error | Error handling pattern (no standard schema.org error type) |
 65: | **HttpTransportConfig** | HTTP-specific transport config | MCP-specific, no schema.org equivalent |
 66: | **ConflictDetectionConfig** | Conflict detection settings | Custom configuration type |
 67: | **ConflictCheckOptions** | Runtime conflict check options | Custom options type |
 68: 
 69: ### Tool Input Types (12 types)
 70: 
 71: All tool input types (`ListCalendarsInput`, `CreateEventInput`, `UpdateEventInput`, `SearchEventsInput`, etc.) are **MCP protocol-specific** and map to tool operation schemas rather than schema.org types directly. However, their parameters align with corresponding schema.org types:
 72: 
 73: - **Event operations** → [`Event`](https://schema.org/Event) + [`Action`](https://schema.org/Action) subtypes
 74: - **Search operations** → [`SearchAction`](https://schema.org/SearchAction)
 75: - **Batch operations** → Custom MCP batch action pattern
 76: 
 77: ---
 78: 
 79: ## Schema.org Type Recommendations
 80: 
 81: ### Core Recommendations (High Priority)
 82: 
 83: #### 1. **Event** (for CalendarEvent)
 84: - **URL**: https://schema.org/Event
 85: - **Usage**: Primary mapping for `CalendarEvent` interface
 86: - **Key Properties**:
 87:   - `name` → `CalendarEvent.summary`
 88:   - `startDate` / `startTime` → `CalendarEvent.start`
 89:   - `endDate` / `endTime` → `CalendarEvent.end`
 90:   - `location` → `CalendarEvent.location`
 91:   - `attendee` → `CalendarEvent.attendees[]`
 92:   - `organizer` → Calendar owner
 93:   - `reminder` → Event reminders (custom extension)
 94: 
 95: **Example Schema.org Event Context**:
 96: ```json
 97: {
 98:   "@context": "https://schema.org",
 99:   "@type": "Event",
100:   "name": "Team Standup",
101:   "startDate": "2026-03-24T10:00:00",
102:   "endDate": "2026-03-24T10:30:00",
103:   "location": "Conference Room A",
104:   "attendee": [
105:     {
106:       "@type": "Person",
107:       "name": "John Doe",
108:       "email": "john@example.com"
109:     }
110:   ],
111:   "organizer": {
112:     "@type": "Person",
113:     "name": "Alice Smith"
114:   }
115: }
116: ```
117: 
118: #### 2. **Person** (for CalendarEventAttendee)
119: - **URL**: https://schema.org/Person
120: - **Usage**: Represents calendar attendees
121: - **Key Properties**:
122:   - `name` → Attendee name
123:   - `email` → Attendee email
124:   - `url` → Calendar profile URL (if available)
125: 
126: #### 3. **Schedule** (for FreeBusyResponse / EventTimeRange)
127: - **URL**: https://schema.org/Schedule
128: - **Usage**: Represents availability and time slots
129: - **Key Properties**:
130:   - `byDay` → Days of availability
131:   - `startTime` → Time availability start
132:   - `endTime` → Time availability end
133: 
134: #### 4. **SearchAction** (for Gmail search operations)
135: - **URL**: https://schema.org/SearchAction
136: - **Usage**: Represents email search operations
137: - **Key Properties**:
138:   - `query` → Search query string
139:   - `result` → Search results (EmailMessage objects)
140: 
141: ### Secondary Recommendations (Medium Priority)
142: 
143: #### 5. **Reservation** (for CalendarEventAttendee + RSVP status)
144: - **URL**: https://schema.org/Reservation
145: - **Usage**: Enhanced representation of event attendance with RSVP status
146: - **Key Properties**:
147:   - `reservationFor` → Calendar Event
148:   - `underName` → Person (attendee)
149:   - `reservationStatus` → RSVP status (Confirmed/Tentative/Declined)
150: 
151: #### 6. **EmailMessage** (for Gmail operations)
152: - **URL**: https://schema.org/EmailMessage
153: - **Usage**: Represents email messages from Gmail
154: - **Key Properties**:
155:   - `sender` → Email sender
156:   - `toRecipient` → Recipients
157:   - `subject` → Email subject
158:   - `dateReceived` → Received timestamp
159: 
160: #### 7. **PerformanceMetric** (for monitoring/observability)
161: - **URL**: https://schema.org/PerformanceMetric
162: - **Usage**: Operation performance tracking
163: - **Key Properties**:
164:   - `name` → Metric name (e.g., "create_event_duration")
165:   - `value` → Metric value (ms)
166:   - `unitText` → "milliseconds"
167: 
168: #### 8. **SoftwareApplication** (for MCP server metadata)
169: - **URL**: https://schema.org/SoftwareApplication
170: - **Usage**: Server metadata (`get_server_metadata` tool)
171: - **Key Properties**:
172:   - `name` → "bot-army-google-calendar-mcp"
173:   - `version` → Semantic version
174:   - `applicationCategory` → "DeveloperApplication"
175:   - `featureList` → Array of tool names
176: 
177: ### Custom Extensions (Not in Schema.org)
178: 
