346: ## Example: CalendarEvent → Event Conversion
347: 
348: ### Current Type (CalendarEvent)
349: ```typescript
350: interface CalendarEvent {
351:   id?: string | null;
352:   summary?: string | null;
353:   start?: {
354:     dateTime?: string | null;
355:     date?: string | null;
356:     timeZone?: string | null;
357:   };
358:   end?: {
359:     dateTime?: string | null;
360:     date?: string | null;
361:     timeZone?: string | null;
362:   };
363:   location?: string | null;
364:   attendees?: CalendarEventAttendee[] | null;
365:   colorId?: string | null;
366:   reminders?: CalendarEventReminder[] | null;
367: }
368: ```
369: 
370: ### Schema.org Equivalent (Event)
371: ```json
372: {
373:   "@context": "https://schema.org",
374:   "@type": "Event",
375:   "identifier": "event-id-123",
376:   "name": "Team Standup",
377:   "startDate": "2026-03-24T10:00:00-07:00",
378:   "endDate": "2026-03-24T10:30:00-07:00",
379:   "location": {
380:     "@type": "Place",
381:     "name": "Conference Room A"
382:   },
383:   "attendee": [
384:     {
385:       "@type": "Person",
386:       "name": "John Doe",
387:       "email": "john@example.com"
388:     }
389:   ],
390:   "color": "blue",
391:   "reminder": {
392:     "@type": "Reminder",
393:     "method": "email",
394:     "minutes": 15
395:   }
396: }
397: ```
398: 
399: ### Mapping Details
400: 
401: | CalendarEvent Field | Event Property | Conversion Notes |
402: |---|---|---|
403: | `id` | `identifier` | 1:1 mapping |
404: | `summary` | `name` | 1:1 mapping |
405: | `start.dateTime` | `startDate` | Convert to ISO 8601 with timezone |
406: | `start.date` | `startDate` | All-day event (no time component) |
407: | `start.timeZone` | Timezone suffix in `startDate` | e.g., `2026-03-24T10:00:00-07:00` |
408: | `end.dateTime` | `endDate` | Convert to ISO 8601 with timezone |
409: | `end.date` | `endDate` | All-day event |
410: | `end.timeZone` | Timezone suffix in `endDate` | e.g., `2026-03-24T10:30:00-07:00` |
411: | `location` | `location` | Wrap string in Place object if needed |
412: | `attendees[]` | `attendee[]` | Each attendee → Person object |
413: | `colorId` | `color` | Direct string mapping |
414: | `reminders[]` | `reminder` | Create custom Reminder objects (or use Action) |
