190: ### Email Organization & Filtering Scripts
191: 
192: Automated scripts for organizing and filtering large volumes of Gmail with focus on correctness and efficiency.
193: 
194: **Management Scripts:** (use shared `createGmailClient()` for OAuth, error handling, and multi-account support)
195: - `list-unread-emails.mjs` - Categorize and summarize unread emails by label/sender patterns; clean fallback categorization
196: - `summarize-remaining.mjs` - Summary of uncategorized/remaining unread emails (internal work, forums, misc); parallel fetching
197: - `describe-internal.mjs` - Detailed breakdown of internal team emails with subjects and dates; hardcoded summary removed
198: - `apply-filters-to-unread.mjs` - Apply existing filters to current unread emails
199: - `create-remaining-filters.mjs` - Batch create filters for multiple categories (Product Updates, Communities, Services)
200: 
201: **Specialized Filters:**
202: - `create-billing-filter.mjs` - Smart billing filter with conditional rate-limit detection
203: - `create-signoz-filter.mjs` - Archive SigNoz monitoring alerts automatically
204: - `create-dmarc-filter.mjs` - Organize DMARC authentication reports
205: - `create-eventbrite-filter.mjs` - Label and archive Eventbrite event emails
206: - `create-meet-notes-filter.mjs` - Label Google Meet notes
207: - `delete-sentry-filter.mjs` - Remove outdated filters
208: 
209: **Archive & Processing Scripts:**
210: - `archive-signoz-dmarc.mjs` - Batch archive monitoring and DMARC report emails using Gmail batch API
211: - `mark-signoz-read.mjs` - Mark SigNoz alerts as read in bulk
212: - `mark-past-events-read.mjs` - Classify event emails by date and mark past events as read
213: - `protect-important-inbox.mjs` - Label critical items to prevent archiving (payments, rate limits, services)
214: 
215: **Event Management:**
216: - `filter-events-by-date.mjs` - Classify event emails as future (label + keep) or past (label + archive)
217: - `organize-international-house.mjs` - Label and organize International House event emails
218: 
219: **Utilities:**
220: - `lib/gmail-client.mjs` - Authenticated Gmail API client factory. Centralizes OAuth2 init, token validation, and multi-account support:
221:   ```js
222:   import { createGmailClient } from './lib/gmail-client.mjs';
223:   const gmail = createGmailClient(); // Uses ACCOUNT_MODE env var, throws on missing tokens
224:   ```
225: - `lib/gmail-label-utils.mjs` - Label ID resolution (NEW in v1.4.9). Resolves hardcoded label IDs dynamically for account portability:
226:   ```js
227:   import { buildLabelCache, resolveLabelId } from './lib/gmail-label-utils.mjs';
228:   const labelCache = await buildLabelCache(gmail);
229:   const labelId = labelCache.get('Events/Community'); // Dynamic instead of hardcoded Label_N
230:   ```
231:   See [`docs/LABEL-RESOLUTION-GUIDE.md`](docs/LABEL-RESOLUTION-GUIDE.md) for complete documentation.
232: - `lib/gmail-batch.mjs` - Batch filter operations for bulk Gmail tasks (10-100x speedup)
233: - `lib/date-based-filter.mjs` - Pure utility for date-based email classification: extracts dates (ISO, US format, text dates, weekday patterns), compares to today, classifies as past/future/unknown. Does not mutate input. Handles dates without year by inferring current or next year.
